bio.summary: Rocca (full name Sébastian Rocca) is a French-Colombian Rapper and Producer born in April 1975. He gained recognition as a rapper during the 1990s as a part of the rap group, La Cliqua.
The Mafia Trece is a French group from Paris, Bagneux and Ivry-sur-Seine. The group is composed by member of the bands Écho du Sud and Moovens'.
Lomepal is a French rapper from the south of Paris.
Alpha Oumar Wann also known as Alpha Wann is a french rapper from Paris (14th). he is a member of L'Entourage & 1995.
Sneazzy is a French rapper from Paris. He is a member of the rap group 1995.
bio.url: Sneazzy is a French rapper, member of 1995

bio.summary: Nusky and Vaati is a french rap duo, composed of Vaati (producer) and Nusky (rapper).
Ken Samaras (born 3 April 1990), better known by his stage name Nekfeu, is a French rapper and record producer who is also a member of the collective L'entourage, and the rap group 1995.
TTC is a French hip hop group from Paris. It consists of Tido Berman, Teki Latex, Cuizinier, Orgasmic, Para One, and Tacteel.
Noir Fluo is french rap band from Paris formed by Emotion Lafolie, Tony Lunettes, Riski & Waslo Dilleggi.
Svinkels is a french Hip Hop band composed of three MCs : Gérard Baste, Nikus Pokus, et Mr. Xavier (alias XanaX), active between 1994 and 2009.
Michaël Eveno, better known by his stage name Grems (born 25 October 1978), is a French rapper and producer of French hip hop and designer.
Lonepsi (born Lindo Gargiulo, 1994), is a French rapper/singer from Parius.
Riski (also known as Riski Metekson and Metek ), born Manuel Goldman in 1979, is a french rapper, author from Paris. He was part of the group Noir Fluo.
ATK is a French rap band from Paris. Created in 1995 and mainly know for their album Heptagone (1998). The group is composed of Axis, Cyanure, Freko Ding', Test and Fredy K.
Mohamed Bellahmed, better know as Moha La Squale (born 24 February 1995) , is a French rapper from the 20th district of Paris.
Matthieu Balanca, known as Gérard Baste, born on January 9, 1973, is a French rapper from Paris. He is a member of the Svinkels rap group.

Les X (previously les X-Men) is a frencg rap band, from Ménilmontant, a neighborhood in the XXe borough of Paris. The group is composed by Hill G (Ill) and Cassidy, and Hi-Fi at the begining. The groups was part of the Time Bomb crew.
Guillaume N'Goumou better know has Pit Baccardi, born 9 june 1978 in Cameroun, is a french rapper & producer from Paris. Pit Baccardi is the half brother of the rapper Dosseh.
Rayan Sanches or Rayan Rockfeller also has Swagg Man is a french rapper from Paris.
Triptik is a french Hip Hop band formed by two rappers Dabaaz and Black' Boul (Greg Frite) and one dj Drixxxé.
Younès Latifi (born 5 February 1984), better known by his stage name Mister You, is a French rapper from Belleville, Paris (19th).

Mohamed Sylla (born 28 November 1994), better known by his stage name MHD is a French rapper from the 19th arrondissement of Paris. His music is the precursor of "Afro Trap", a mixture of African music and Trap music.
Oxmo Puccino (born Abdoulaye Diarra; 3 August 1974) is a hip hop musician born in Mali.
Joe Lucazz is a french rapper. He is a member of the Neochrome label.
Fabrice "Fabe" (born in 1971 Paris, France) is a French rapper from 10th District of Paris. He is one of the founders of Scred Connexion.
Hedi Chabar better know has Brulux is a french rapper from Paris.
Coyote Jo Bastard is a French rapper from the 17ème arrondissement of Paris.

La Cliqua was a French hip hop group. Its members are Rocca, a bilingual French rapper with Colombian roots, Kohndo (formerly known as Doc Odnok), Daddy Lord C, Egosyst (Aarafat), Raphaël (Raphton), Dj Jelahee (Gallegos), Lumumba, Le Chimiste and Mush le Phonky Bwana.
Scred Connexion is a French rap collective launched in the 1990s composed by Fabe, Koma, Haroun, Mokless and Morad, with the assistance of Butch.
Georges Édouard Nicolo know has Georgio (21/01/1993), is a french rapper from Paris (18th).

Hyacinthe is a French rapper from crew DFHDGB (which stands for "Des Faux Hipster et Des Grosses Bites" and means "False Hipsters and Big Dicks") composed of rapper LOAS and beatmaker Krampf. His first album "Sarah" is out on September 29, 2017.
Davodka is a french rapper from Paris (18th arrondissemen). He is a member of the crew Mentalités Sons Dangereux.
Doc Gynéco, real name, Bruno Beausir, is a French hip hop artist of Guadeloupean origin. His music is typically characterized as a ragga/rap style, that has found its fan base in France.
Assassin is a French rap group formed in the 18th Arrondissement of Paris. The group was formed in 1985 by Rockin' Squat and Solo.
Mohamed Mehadji know has Morsay, (born 19/08 1980). Is a french rapper know for is internet video.
La Clinique is a French hiphop group originally created by Doc Gynéco and joined by Doom Décadent, Space L'Anesthésiste, Les Sales Gosses, Papillon, Charlie Waits and Psychologue.
Hugo TSR (previously know has Hugo Boss) is a french rappeur from La Chapelle,  Paris (18th). He is one of the member of the TSR Crew.
A2h is a french rapper, producer from Melun.
Daddy Lord C, real name Clarck Ebara, born 7 january 1970, is a french rapper & boxer from Nemours, Seinte-et-Marne. He was one of the member of the rap band La Cliqua.
Mystik born Ghislain Loussingui Diabaka in 1978 at Pointe-Noire (Congo). Is a french rapper from Meaux (Seine et Marne). He was a member of the Bisso Na Bisso group.
Djadja & Dinaz is a French hip-hop duo from Meaux.
O'Rosko Raricim born in 1978 in Congo. Is a french rapper from Meaux (Seine et Marne). He was a member of the Ghetto Fabulous Gang.
Bastos is French rapper from Chelles (Seine et Marne).
2 Bal 2 Neg is a french rap group from Chelles. The group is composed by the   twin brother Doc TMC et G-Kill.
Lemdi & Moax are two MC from Val Maubuée. They are member of the Val Mobb Industries crew.
Fuzati (born in 1978) is a French rapper originating from Versailles. He was co-founder in 2000 of Klub des Loosers.
L'Skadrille is a French rap band from Saint-Cyr-l'École, Yvelines. Formed in 1996 by 13or (Trésor) et 16ar (César).
Laouni Mouhid (born December 25, 1981 in Trappes, Yvelines), commonly known by his stage name La Fouine or Fouiny Baby, is a French rapper.
La Rumeur is a French-language rap group from Élancourt (Yvelines, France). The group is composed of four rappers, Ekoué, Hamé, Mourad, and Philippe, and two DJs, Kool M and Soul G.
Gaël Faye is a French rapper and singer of Burundian origin from the Yvelines, France.
Youssoupha Mabiki, better known by his nickname Youssoupha born in Kinshasa on 29 August 1979) is a French rapper of Congolese origin.
Ninho is a french rapper from Yerres, Essone.
Juicy P is a french Rapper from Grigny.
Thomas Idir a.k.a. Sinik (born June 26, 1980) is a French rap artist. His father is Algerian while his mother is French.
Diam's (born Mélanie Georgiades on 25 July 1980) is a French-language rap artist of French and Greek Cypriot origin from Essone. She gained notoriety in France in the 2000.
Stan Dinga Pinto, better known by the artistic name Niska, is a french rapper from Évry, Essonne.
Eloquence is a french rapper from Evry, Esonne.
Atef Kahlaoui know has Alkpote is a French Rapper from Evry.
Koba la D is a french rapper from Evry, Essonne.
Freddy Kpadé know has Ol Kainry, is a french rapper from Courcouronnes, Essonne.
Sérigne M'Baye Gueye (born 28 March 1978), better known by his stage name Disiz, (formerly Disiz la Peste and Disiz Peter Punk), is a French rapper and actor from Évry.
PNL (Peace N' Lovés, translated Peace and money) is an independent French rap group formed in 2014 by two brothers, Ademo and N.O.S from Corbeil-Essonnes.
Guizmo, born on January 21, 1991, is a French rapper from Villeneuve-la-Garenne. He was a member of the collective of rap l'Entourage.
Kekra is a french rapper from Courbevoie, Hauts-de-Seine.
Elie Yaffa (born December 9, 1976), better known under his stage name Booba is a French rapper from Boulogne Billancourt.
Daniel Lakoué better know has Dany Dan, is a french rapper, (born 20 November 1973). He is one of the member of the group les Sages Poètes de la Rue.
Jean-Jacques Kodjo, a.k.a. Zoxea, was born on November 11, 1974 in Sèvres, Hauts-de-Seine.
Mala is a French rapper from Pont de Sèvres, Boulogne-Billandcourt. He was a member of the rap group Malekal Morte.

Dijibi Diop (Better known has Boulox) was a French rapper from Pont-de-Sèvre (Boulogne-Billancourt, Paris). He was one of the original member of the Mo'vez Lang group, with LIM, Cens Nino, Kaizer and Furax. He passed away in 2016 due to medical issues.
Salim Lakhdari (born in July, 1979 in Boulogne-Billancourt (Paris), France), more commonly known as LIM, is a French rapper and producer of Kabyle Algerian origin.
Salif Fofana better known by the mononym Salif (born Salif Wonka in 1982), is a French rapper based in Boulogne-Billancourt of Malian and Guadeloupean origin.
Benash is a French rapper from Boulogne-Billancourt, Hauts-de-Seine. He is a member of the 40000 Gang group.
Ali, originally Daddy Ali (born in 1975 at Issy-les-Moulineaux, France) is a French rapper of Moroccan origin.
Hornet La Frappe is French rapper from Épinay-sur-Seine, Seine-Saint-Denis.
Valéry François know has Busta Flex, (born 30 september 1977) is a french rapper from Val-d'Oise.
Alpha 5.20 is an French rapper, from Épinay-sur-Seine, Seine-Saint-Denis. He is the leader of the Ghetto Fabulous Gang.
Maes is a French rapper from Sevran, Seine-Saint-Denis.
13 Block is a french Hip Hop group from Sevran,  Seine-Saint-Denis. The group is composed of DeTess, OldPee, Zefor, et Zed.
Dinos Punchlinovic is a French rapper from La Courneuve, Seine-Saint-Denis.

Sadek Bourghuiba (born 25 May 1991) and known by the mononym Sadek is a French rapper from Neuilly-Plaisance. He also uses the pseudonym Johnny Niuuum or Sadek Niuum. He is signed to the French Hostile record label.
Socrate Petteng better known as Mac Tyer is a French rapper of Cameroonian descent, born in Aubervilliers, Seine-Saint-Denis. Alongside with Mac Kregor he is a member of the rap band Tandem.
Youssef Soukouna (born 20 April 1981), better known by his stage name Sefyu is a French rapper of Senegalese descent from Aulnay-sous-Bois, Seine-Saint-Denis.
Valentin Le Du, know has Vald (born 15 jully 1992) is a French rapper from Aulnay-sous-Bois, Seine-Saint-Denis.
Nakk, real name Narcisse Kamga, born the 30 march 1976, is a french rapper from Bobigny, Seine-Saint-Denis.
Sofiane Zermani (born 21 July 1986) better known by the mononym Sofiane is a French rapper of Algerian origin. He is also known by the name Fianso. He come from Le Blanc-Mesni, Seine-Saint-Denis.
Kalash Criminel is a French rapper of Congolese descent from Sevran, Seine-Saint-Denis.
Nikarson Saint-Germain better known by his stage name Alibi Montana (born in Villetaneuse, Seine-Saint-Denis, France in 1978) is a French rapper of Haitian origin.
Tandem was a French rap band from Aubervilliers, Seine-Saint-Denis formed by Mac Tyer, de Mac Kregor et & Mac Thyff.

Suprême NTM (or simply NTM) is a French hip hop group formed in 1989 in the Seine-Saint-Denis département. The group comprises rappers Joey Starr (born Didier Morville) and Kool Shen (born Bruno Lopes).

Kamel Jdayni Houari (born in Le Kremlin-Bicêtre on 13 May 1980) better known as Kamelancien later shortened into Kamelanc', is a francophone rapper of Moroccan origin. He grew up in Le Kremlin-Bicêtre, a town in the suburbs of Paris.
Karim Zenoud better known by his stage name Lacrim at times stylized as LaCrim is a French rapper from Algerian origins.
113 is a French hip hop group with African and Caribbean roots originating in North and West Africa and the island of Guadeloupe, formed in the Parisian suburb of Vitry-sur-Seine.
Mafia K-1 Fry sometimes stylized as Mafia K'1 Fry is a French collective of hip hop rappers from the Val-de-Marne and the Orly-Choisy-Vitry-Joinville axis, south of Paris.
Abdelkrim Brahmi a.k.a. Rim'K (born 21 June 1978 in Paris, France) is a French rapper of Algerian descent. Rim'K was raised in the Parisian suburb of Vitry-sur-Seine.
Alix Mathurin (born 28 December 1977) better known as Kery James, is a French rapper from Orly.
Housni Mkouboi better known as Rohff at times stylized as Roh2f (born in Antananarivo, Madagascar on 15 December 1977) is a French rapper.
Claude M'Barali better known by his stage name MC Solaar (born March 5, 1969) is a French hip hop and rap artist with Senegalese and Chadian origins.
Nabil Sahli (born 16 August 1978), better known by his stage name Nessbeal, is a French rapper from Villiers-sur-Marne, Val-de-Marne.
Nicolas Salvadori (born in Saint-Ouen-l'Aumône, Val-d'Oise, France on 27 October 1980), better known by his stage name Seth Gueko, is a French rapper.

Sniper is a French hip hop band from the Val-d'Oise department consisting of Tunisiano (Bachir Baccour) and Aketo (Ryad Selmi). Blacko, also known as Afrikaf (Karl Appela), was a member of the group until his departure in July 2007.
Stomy Bugsy born Gilles Duarte (21 May 1972) is a French rapper and actor from Sarcelles, France. He is a member of the group Minister AMER with the rapper Passi.

Passi Balende better know has Passi is a French hip hop artist who became famous in the mid-1990s with the group Ministère AMER, which included himself and Stomy Bugsy. He is most widely known, however, as a solo artist.
The Ministère AMER (Action, Musique Et Rap) is a French hip hop group from Sarcelles, consisting of the rappers Passi and Stomy Bugsy, DJ Ghetch, and the producer/manager Kenzy.
Nèg' Marrons is french hip-hop & reggae group from Garges-Sarcelles, Val-d'Oise. They was part of the Secteur A crew.
Driver is a French rapper, actor from Sarcelles (Val-d'Oise) born in 1976. Better know for is song Aie Aie Aie on the album "Le grand schelem".
Ärsenik is a rap group based in Villiers-le-Bel, France, founded in 1992, and made up of two brothers, Lino (Gaëlino M'Bani) and Calbo (Calboni M'Bani), whose family is originally from Congo.
Gaëlino M'Bani better known by his stage name Lino is a French rapper. He was a member of the French rap duo Ärsenik with his brother Calboni M'Bani known as Calbo in the duo.
